# Pre-commit quality gates

**Before creating any commit**, run the checks that CI will run. Do not rely on partial checks (e.g. typecheck or quality alone).

From repo root:

```bash
bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh
npm run build:native
bash scripts/ci/run-pr-tests-full.sh
```

Or the all-in-one local mirror:

```bash
npm run build:native
npm run ci:verify:checks
```

## What each step covers

| Step | Mirrors CI job | Catches |
|------|----------------|---------|
| `run-pr-quality.sh` | Typecheck & lint | `npm ci` + **`fix-rollup-native.sh`**, eslint, tsc, **`run-helpers-unit-tests.sh`**, **Sherpa example `tsc`** ([`run-sherpa-example-ci.sh typecheck`](../../scripts/ci/run-sherpa-example-ci.sh)) |
| `build:native` | Compile native | Stale `.node` missing new NAPI methods (e.g. `setOnIceGatheringStateChange`) |
| `run-pr-tests-full.sh` | Quality + Test | `cargo test`, `npm test`, **Sherpa `start:roundtrip-barge-in`** (downloads EN models on first run) |

`run-pr-tests-full.sh` = `run-pr-quality.sh` + `run-pr-integration.sh`. On macOS, `build:native` produces the host debug `.node` that `npm test` loads.

### When to run

| Changed paths | Required before commit |
|---------------|------------------------|
| `packages/sdk/`, `packages/signaling/`, `examples/` | **`run-pr-quality.sh`** + **`build:native`** + **`run-pr-tests-full.sh`** (includes Sherpa typecheck + barge-in E2E); SDK/bindings: also **`build-ts-workspace.sh`** / **`verify-release-publish-ts.sh`** |
| `examples/voice-agent-local-sherpa/` only | **`run-pr-quality.sh`** at minimum (eslint + Sherpa typecheck); full parity needs **`run-pr-tests-full.sh`** + models |
| `packages/helpers/`, `packages/sdk/`, `packages/signaling/`, multi-client example | **`npm run ci:pre-push`** (lint + **build-ts-workspace** + vitest) or full **`npm run ci:quality`** |
| `packages/sdk/src/**` (types/exports) | Also run **`bash scripts/ci/build-ts-workspace.sh`** — see [`sdk-build.mdc`](sdk-build.mdc) |
| `packages/bindings/`, `crates/` | **quality + build:native + tests** (rebuild native after bindings changes) |
| `scripts/ci/`, `.github/` | `npm run ci:verify:checks` |

### Common mistakes

- **`npm run typecheck` is not enough** — no eslint; no vitest/cargo tests; no `build-ts-workspace.sh` (release publish compiles SDK against npm-installed bindings unless `paths` override).
- **`run-pr-quality.sh` alone is not enough for SDK/bindings** — see [`release-ts-build.mdc`](release-ts-build.mdc); run **`build-ts-workspace.sh`** or **`verify-release-publish-ts.sh`** (CI **Build TypeScript** job does this once).
- **`run-pr-quality.sh` alone is not enough** — TS-only commits can pass quality but fail Test when CI loads a stale cached `.node` without new native exports.
- **`ci:pre-push` without `build-ts-workspace` used to miss CI failures** — helpers vitest skipped compile when local `dist/` existed; quality job runs on a clean tree. Always run `ci:pre-push` or `ci:quality` before push when touching helpers/sdk/signaling.
- **Rebuild native after changing `packages/bindings/` or `crates/`** before `npm test`.

### Before push / PR

**Required for helpers/sdk/signaling changes** (matches CI Typecheck & lint on a fresh checkout):

```bash
npm run ci:pre-push          # scoped: lint + build-ts-workspace + vitest
# or full CI quality job:
npm run ci:quality           # bash scripts/ci/run-pr-quality.sh
```

Install once so pushes cannot skip this accidentally:

```bash
bash scripts/ci/install-pre-push-hook.sh
```

`ci:pre-push` rebuilds the TS workspace when `packages/helpers|sdk|signaling/` changed — stale local `dist/` alone used to pass while CI failed.

Re-run the **full** sequence (`run-pr-quality.sh`, `build:native`, `run-pr-tests-full.sh`) if the commit touched Rust, bindings, or you need integration parity.
